.TH "ccw_device_pnso" 9 "ccw_device_pnso" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ccw_device_pnso \- Perform Network-Subchannel Operation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ccw_device_pnso
.BI "(struct ccw_device *cdev "  ","
.BI "struct chsc_pnso_area *pnso_area "  ","
.BI "u8 oc "  ","
.BI "struct chsc_pnso_resume_token resume_token "  ","
.BI "int cnc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cdev" 12
device on which PNSO is performed
.IP "pnso_area" 12
request and response block for the operation
.IP "oc" 12
Operation Code
.IP "resume_token" 12
resume token for multiblock response
.IP "cnc" 12
Boolean change-notification control
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
pnso_area must be allocated by the caller with get_zeroed_page(GFP_KERNEL)

Returns 0 on success.
